#: xml/release-notes.xml:696(title)
msgid "No Default Compose Key Combination"
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:697(para)
msgid "In previous versions of openSUSE, the compose key combination allowed typing characters that were not part of the regular keyboard layout. For example, to produce <quote>Ã¥</quote>, you could press and release <keycombo><keycap function=\"shift\"/><keycap>Right Ctrl</keycap></keycombo> and then press <keycap>a</keycap> twice."
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:704(para)
msgid "In openSUSE Leap 15.0, there is no longer a predefined compose key combination because <keycombo><keycap function=\"shift\"/><keycap>Right Ctrl</keycap></keycombo> does not work as expected anymore."
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:712(para)
msgid "To define a system-wide custom compose key combination, use the file <filename>/etc/X11/Xmodmap</filename> and look for the following lines:"
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:716(screen)
#, no-wrap
msgid "[...]\n!! Third example: Change right Control key to Compose key.\n!! To do Compose Character, press this key and afterwards two\n!! characters (e.g. `a' and `^' to get 342).\n!remove  Control  = Control_R\n!keysym Control_R = Multi_key\n!add     Control  = Control_R\n[...]"
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:724(para)
msgid "To uncomment the example code, remove the <literal>!</literal> characters at the beginning of lines. However, note that the setup from <filename>Xmodmap</filename> will be overwritten if you are using <command>setxkbmap</command>."
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:732(para)
msgid "To define a user-specific compose key combination, use your desktop's keyboard configuration tool or the command-line tool <command>setxkbmap</command>:"
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:738(replaceable)
msgid "[...]"
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:738(replaceable)
msgid "COMPOSE_KEY"
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:737(screen)
#, no-wrap
msgid "\nsetxkbmap <placeholder-1/> -option compose:<placeholder-2/>\n     "
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:740(para)
msgid "For the variable <replaceable>COMPOSE_KEY</replaceable>, use your preferred character, for example <literal>ralt</literal>, <literal>lwin</literal>, <literal>rwin</literal>, <literal>menu</literal>, <literal>rctl</literal>, or <literal>caps</literal>."
msgstr ""

#: xml/release-notes.xml:749(para)
msgid "Alternatively, use an IBus input method that allows typing the characters you need without a Compose key."
